Not a thing. Nada.

251
00:13:11,103 --> 00:13:12,104
It's too soon.

252
00:13:12,104 --> 00:13:13,689
I haven't had a
chance to train yet.

253
00:13:13,689 --> 00:13:15,816
So, not only would
I be useless,

254
00:13:15,816 --> 00:13:19,528
I'd probably just end up
making things worse.

255
00:13:19,528 --> 00:13:21,655
And with thugs like that
it's really better to just

256
00:13:21,655 --> 00:13:24,491
give 'em what they want.

257
00:13:24,491 --> 00:13:25,659
I know!

258
00:13:25,659 --> 00:13:27,244
I think there's a chapter
on this sort of thing

259
00:13:27,244 --> 00:13:29,455
in my Urban Survival Handbook!

260
00:13:29,455 --> 00:13:30,623
It's at home...

261
00:13:30,623 --> 00:13:31,874
You fool!

262
00:13:31,874 --> 00:13:33,167
You shouldn't be
searching through a book

263
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,543
at a time like this!

264
00:13:34,543 --> 00:13:37,004
How can I be so stupid...!

265
00:13:37,004 --> 00:13:39,632
That's my classmate over
there, she needs my help!

266
00:13:39,632 --> 00:13:41,508
I saw it. You pushed him.

267
00:13:41,508 --> 00:13:44,929
Where do you get off slamming an
old man to the ground like that?

268
00:13:44,929 --> 00:13:46,305
Calm down four-eyes.

269
00:13:46,305 --> 00:13:48,515
He was wandering down the
street in everybody's way,

270
00:13:48,515 --> 00:13:49,683
so we shoved him aside.

271
00:13:49,683 --> 00:13:51,518
Well that piece of
junk you call a car

272
00:13:51,518 --> 00:13:52,937
is in everybody's way too.

273
00:13:52,937 --> 00:13:53,812
Are you gonna do--

274
00:13:53,812 --> 00:13:56,607
Oh no, arguing with them is
only going to make it worse.

275
00:13:56,607 --> 00:13:58,901
We'll park our car
wherever we want.

276
00:13:58,901 --> 00:14:02,154
And anybody that's got any
sense will stay out of our way.

277
00:14:02,154 --> 00:14:05,783
Especially pretty little
blonde girls like yourself.

278
00:14:05,783 --> 00:14:08,702
Yeah, nobody tells
us what to do.

279
00:14:08,702 --> 00:14:10,371
Why don't you have
yourself a look?

280
00:14:10,371 --> 00:14:12,998
Those people understand
what the score is.

281
00:14:12,998 --> 00:14:17,711
You see all of them
pretending not to notice us.

282
00:14:17,711 --> 00:14:19,213
Well I'm not one of them.

283
00:14:19,213 --> 00:14:20,714
Apologize now.

284
00:14:20,714 --> 00:14:22,216
You little brat...

285
00:14:22,216 --> 00:14:25,135
They're going to bully you just
like they did in junior high.

286
00:14:25,135 --> 00:14:26,220
You're weak.

287
00:14:26,220 --> 00:14:27,805
That will never change.

288
00:14:27,805 --> 00:14:29,306
Accept it.

289
00:14:29,306 --> 00:14:32,017
You're never gonna be strong,
no matter how hard you try.

290
00:14:32,017 --> 00:14:34,478
You're a loser! You're
always be a loser!

291
00:14:34,478 --> 00:14:36,105
And guys like me are
gonna step on you

292
00:14:36,105 --> 00:14:37,606
for the rest of your
worthless life!

293
00:14:37,606 --> 00:14:39,525
I'm about to bloody that
pretty mouth of yours.

294
00:14:39,525 --> 00:14:40,442
Aggh!

295
00:14:40,442 --> 00:14:44,196
Let go of her now!

296
00:14:48,325 --> 00:14:50,786
Aahh! Fists of fury!

297
00:14:50,786 --> 00:14:51,996
Who's this dude?

298
00:14:51,996 --> 00:14:53,372
Hurry get out of here Miu!

299
00:14:53,372 --> 00:14:57,710
I can only hold them
back for so long--

300
00:14:57,710 --> 00:15:01,255
Okay kid, now your dead.

301
00:15:01,255 --> 00:15:03,007
You just made the biggest,
and last, mistake

302
00:15:03,007 --> 00:15:05,676
of your life kid.
You know who we are?

303
00:15:05,676 --> 00:15:07,428
Well, no, I don't
know who you are.

304
00:15:07,428 --> 00:15:08,887
Sorry, I wasn't
thinking clearly.

305
00:15:08,887 --> 00:15:11,056
I just acted on instinct.
It was a mistake.

306
00:15:11,056 --> 00:15:13,851
Seriously, I didn't mean to...

307
00:15:13,851 --> 00:15:15,519
Wait! You can't use that!

308
00:15:15,519 --> 00:15:17,521
I'm unarmed! That's
against the rules!

309
00:15:17,521 --> 00:15:19,773
We're playing by
different rule books kid.

310
00:15:19,773 --> 00:15:22,317
And mine says you ain't
to live no longer.

311
00:15:22,317 --> 00:15:23,027
Hold him down!

312
00:15:23,027 --> 00:15:26,280
Nooooooooooo!

313
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:33,787
--Where'd she go?!
--She used me as a spring board.

314
00:15:36,373 --> 00:15:38,667
Okay, now you've made me mad.

315
00:15:38,667 --> 00:15:40,919
Whoa... I barely had
a chance to blink,

316
00:15:40,919 --> 00:15:42,838
and she hit all
three of those guys!

317
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:03,692
Amazing. That was intense.

318
00:16:03,692 --> 00:16:09,490
What is she? Some kind of killer
ballerina or something?

319
00:16:09,490 --> 00:16:11,617
That was impressive. Thank you.

320
00:16:11,617 --> 00:16:13,786
You've rescued me
twice in one day.

321
00:16:13,786 --> 00:16:16,455
Oh.,yeah, sure thing,
it was my pleasure...

322
00:16:16,455 --> 00:16:19,041
Wait, but that's
not what happened.

323
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:21,335
That took a lot of guts
back there, Kenichi.

324
00:16:21,335 --> 00:16:23,962
You know I don't think I could
have found a better person

325
00:16:23,962 --> 00:16:25,589
to be my first new friend.

326
00:16:25,589 --> 00:16:27,382
Wait? So we're friends?

327
00:16:27,382 --> 00:16:28,467
Of course!

328
00:16:31,906 --> 00:16:33,199
The Karate Club huh?

329
00:16:33,199 --> 00:16:35,660
I could tell you were a
martial artist from your collar.

330
00:16:35,660 --> 00:16:39,581
Well, I don't know
if I'd go that far.

331
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:42,167
Kenichi... I just want you
to know that guy from the club

332
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:44,544
who told you martial arts
is only for the strong,

333
00:16:44,544 --> 00:16:46,296
he doesn't know what
he's talking about.

334
00:16:46,296 --> 00:16:47,797
What do you mean by that?

335
00:16:47,797 --> 00:16:49,883
Um, well I've always
been interested

336
00:16:49,883 --> 00:16:52,635
in martial arts myself, so
I know a little bit about it

337
00:16:52,635 --> 00:16:54,929
Wait a minute, what're you
calling "a little bit."

338
00:16:54,929 --> 00:16:57,474
My Sensai has always
explained it to me like this:

339
00:16:57,474 --> 00:16:59,684
The Martial arts were
originally created

340
00:16:59,684 --> 00:17:01,936
to help the weak fight
against the strong.

341
00:17:01,936 --> 00:17:04,522
That means someone's size isn't
really all that important.

342
00:17:04,522 --> 00:17:07,817
So the guy from the Karate
Club has it backwards.

343
00:17:07,817 --> 00:17:11,237
I could try explaining that, but
I still doubt they'd teach me.

344
00:17:11,237 --> 00:17:13,865
Not only that, but I've got
less than a week until--

345
00:17:13,865 --> 00:17:15,992
Oh wait! My how-to books.

346
00:17:18,203 --> 00:17:20,372
"Practice is the only answer."

347
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:24,042
Man, I'm dead.

348
00:17:24,042 --> 00:17:26,920
Listen, If you're really serious
about getting stronger,

349
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:29,839
then I think I know of a place
where they can help you out,

350
00:17:29,839 --> 00:17:31,508
if you're willing
to give it a try.

351
00:17:31,508 --> 00:17:33,343
You think they teach
me to take out thugs

352
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:34,969
--like you just did?
--I can't answer that.

353
00:17:34,969 --> 00:17:36,846
I can say is that if you
train in this place,

354
00:17:36,846 --> 00:17:39,557
you'll get a lot stronger than
you are right now, guaranteed.

355
00:17:39,557 --> 00:17:40,809
Tell me! Tell me!

356
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:41,684
One thing.

357
00:17:41,684 --> 00:17:42,519
What is it?

358
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:44,104
When I say you'll get stronger,

359
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:47,482
that's assuming you
manage to stay alive...

360
00:17:47,482 --> 00:17:48,691
Huh?

361
00:17:51,277 --> 00:17:52,946
I'm pretty sure
this is the place.

362
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:55,824
I can't believe I
actually found it.

363
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,368
What was Miu thinking
when she made this map?

364
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:01,371
Sprinting? What does that
have to do with directions?

365
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:03,498
And what's with the crazy route?

366
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,168
Okay...

367
00:18:07,168 --> 00:18:09,838
As long as you're
sure about this.

368
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:11,381
Of course I'm sure.

369
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:13,091
I don't have a choice.

370
00:18:13,091 --> 00:18:14,050
One week from now,

371
00:18:14,050 --> 00:18:16,678
I'm gonna be beaten
within inches of my life.

372
00:18:16,678 --> 00:18:19,639
So, I've got nothing to lose.

373
00:18:19,639 --> 00:18:21,433
I'm comin' in!

374
00:18:24,102 --> 00:18:25,645
What's with this gate?

375
00:18:25,645 --> 00:18:27,147
It feels like it's
made of lead.

376
00:18:27,147 --> 00:18:30,692
Come on...
Open uuuuup!

377
00:18:35,155 --> 00:18:36,114
Hello there.

378
00:18:36,114 --> 00:18:39,159
What sort of business do you
have in this place young man?

379
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:41,411
Business! Uh, I
was just leaving!

380
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:45,290
Sorry...

381
00:18:46,207 --> 00:18:47,917
What the--?!
Did you just...

382
00:18:47,917 --> 00:18:49,169
...warp?!

383
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:51,963
How'd ya do that?

384
00:18:51,963 --> 00:18:53,590
Judging by the
look on your face,

385
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:56,050
I'm not sure you could handle
the answer to that question.

386
00:18:56,050 --> 00:18:58,011
Try to calm down a bit.

387
00:18:58,011 --> 00:18:59,220
You wouldn't happen
to be some kind of

388
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:01,264
martial arts
master, would you?

389
00:19:02,515 --> 00:19:04,476
I wouldn't consider
myself a master.

390
00:19:04,476 --> 00:19:05,768
I'm just fortunate.

391
00:19:05,768 --> 00:19:07,937
I have yet to lose
a single battle.

392
00:19:07,937 --> 00:19:08,980
This is it!

393
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:11,274
This is the place
she told me about!

394
00:19:11,274 --> 00:19:13,985
Uh, excuse me sir,
I'm Kenichi Shirahama.

395
00:19:13,985 --> 00:19:15,737
I was sent here
by Miu Furinji.

396
00:19:15,737 --> 00:19:17,864
It's both an honor and
a pleasure to meet you.

397
00:19:17,864 --> 00:19:20,366
That was quite an impressive
introduction young man.

398
00:19:20,366 --> 00:19:21,409
Your manners are excellent,

399
00:19:21,409 --> 00:19:23,620
but there's no need to
be formal around here.

400
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:25,538
So then, Miu sent you, huh?

401
00:19:25,538 --> 00:19:26,956
Yes.

402
00:19:26,956 --> 00:19:27,749
Um, sir?

403
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:29,417
What exactly do you teach here?

404
00:19:29,417 --> 00:19:31,419
I mean, you teach Karate, right?

405
00:19:31,419 --> 00:19:34,005
Hm-mm. Among other things, yes.

406
00:19:34,005 --> 00:19:35,924
That's awesome!

407
00:19:39,552 --> 00:19:42,388
What is that monster and where
on Earth did it come from?

408
00:19:42,388 --> 00:19:44,933
That's Apachai Hopachai,
from Thailand.

409
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,893
Only 28 years old,
believe it or not.

410
00:19:46,893 --> 00:19:48,269
Wowwwww!

411
00:19:48,269 --> 00:19:49,687
Amazing!

412
00:19:57,779 --> 00:20:00,448
Apa! Apa!

413
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,909
Be careful you don't
speak too loud.

414
00:20:02,909 --> 00:20:05,078
If he hears you, he
might start showing off.

415
00:20:05,078 --> 00:20:06,579
ApaApaApaApaApaApaApaApa!

416
00:20:06,579 --> 00:20:08,623
Alright!
That's enough Apachai!

417
00:20:08,623 --> 00:20:11,584
Is he always like this?

418
00:20:11,584 --> 00:20:13,169
We don't get many visitors.

419
00:20:13,169 --> 00:20:15,588
He probably just got
a little over stimulated.

420
00:20:15,588 --> 00:20:19,843
No visitors? What kind
of Dojo is this?

421
00:20:28,059 --> 00:20:30,645
Miu's definitely cute,
but this girl is hot!

422
00:20:30,645 --> 00:20:33,481
Maybe she'll give me
some private lessons.

423
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:39,988
Show yourself! What business
do you have with me?

424
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:40,780
Speak!

425
00:20:40,780 --> 00:20:42,448
Ah, who me?!

426
00:20:42,448 --> 00:20:44,701
Kensei! I know exactly
where you're hiding...

427
00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:46,703
...and so does my sword!

428
00:20:49,038 --> 00:20:50,873
Relax, I was just
passing through,

429
00:20:50,873 --> 00:20:53,376
making sure everything's still
on the up and up, down below.

430
00:20:53,376 --> 00:20:54,586
Looking good.

431
00:20:54,586 --> 00:20:56,880
That doesn't explain the
camera you're holding.

432
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,007
What were you taking
pictures of down there?

433
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:02,135
Uh, what chu mean?!

434
00:21:08,725 --> 00:21:11,853
I wouldn't recommend snooping
around here young man.

435
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:12,729
Now then,

436
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:14,981
I'm about to introduce you
to the Karate teacher

437
00:21:14,981 --> 00:21:17,400
you've been looking for,
but I have to warn you,

438
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,901
he can be difficult.

439
00:21:18,901 --> 00:21:20,236
Um, okay.

440
00:21:20,236 --> 00:21:22,655
Hey, Shio! I need a favor!

441
00:21:25,158 --> 00:21:28,286
Uh uh. No way.

442
00:21:28,286 --> 00:21:31,664
I don't take disciples.

443
00:21:31,664 --> 00:21:33,958
How many times do we
gotta go over this gramps?

444
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:34,834
Told ya.

445
00:21:34,834 --> 00:21:37,211
He dosen't sound like a teacher.

446
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:40,632
It's a bad idea old man.

447
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:43,968
Let's suppose I did let
him become my pupil...

448
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:57,231
He would be dead
in three days time.

449
00:21:57,231 --> 00:22:00,151
You don't say. Well
that's just too bad.

450
00:22:00,151 --> 00:22:03,738
The man obviously doesn't want
to take on a disciple, ah well.

451
00:22:03,738 --> 00:22:06,157
Thanks anyway,
I'll be going now.

452
00:22:12,038 --> 00:22:14,707
This kid seems
kinda high strung.

453
00:22:14,707 --> 00:22:17,460
He's certainly energetic.

454
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:19,379
W-Where am I?

455
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:23,925
What kind of crazy dojo is this?

456
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:27,178
Kenichi? Kenichi?

457
00:22:27,178 --> 00:22:27,804
Miu!

458
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:29,514
You fainted,
you feeling alright?

459
00:22:29,514 --> 00:22:32,767
We-We should get out of here!
This place is really dangerous!

460
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:34,852
This is...
my home...

461
00:22:34,852 --> 00:22:36,813
You see Hayato is...

462
00:22:36,813 --> 00:22:37,855
...her grandfather.

463
00:22:37,855 --> 00:22:40,692
Uh?! Grandfather?!

464
00:22:40,692 --> 00:22:43,069
Okay, right about now that
little voice in my head

465
00:22:43,069 --> 00:22:44,570
is telling me to run for it.

466
00:22:44,570 --> 00:22:46,155
Bad idea! Bad idea!

467
00:22:46,155 --> 00:22:49,325
What the heck am I getting
myself into here?!

468
00:22:49,325 --> 00:22:51,703
I'm dead meat.

469
00:24:19,123 --> 00:24:20,917
Who are all of these
scary-looking people

470
00:24:20,917 --> 00:24:22,585
and what are they
gonna do to me?

471
00:24:22,585 --> 00:24:25,004
Each of them is a master
of a different martial art.

472
00:24:25,004 --> 00:24:28,549
They live and practice
here at Ryozanpaku.

473
00:24:28,549 --> 00:24:31,177
Kenichi, I promise if
you'll let them teach you

474
00:24:31,177 --> 00:24:32,762
they'll help
you get stronger

475
00:24:32,762 --> 00:24:35,681
But I'm not sure that I'm cut
out for this sort of thing!

476
00:24:35,681 --> 00:24:37,225
You'll be fine, Kenichi.

477
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:39,811
I have complete faith
in you. Just go for broke.

478
00:24:39,811 --> 00:24:41,729
No way! Are you kidding me?!

479
00:24:41,729 --> 00:24:44,941
Getting "broke" is exactly
what I'm afraid of!

480
00:24:44,941 --> 00:24:48,277
This is going to be a little
harder than I thought.

